This paper discusses the use of knowledge organization systems (KOS) in the Semantic Web, which involves information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of Linked Open Data (LOD) and ontologies, which are relevant to the sub-categories of deep learning (DL), databases (DB), and social and information networks (SI).
